We're on a mission to help everyone eat better and save more.Website Link:  http://stretchrecipes.com/about/Blog Link: http://stretchrecipes.com/blog/We're starting by building a Food App that will help you eat better and save more without lots of planning and without blowing your budget.  Stret¢h pairs your cash on hand or budget with delicious, easy to make nutritional chef recipes and coupons.  PRE-ORDER THE COMPLETED APP NOW BY CONTRIBUTING $1This app will be available for Web, iOS, and Android.  Here's a concept drawing:How does Stret¢h work?:
Enter your budget or cash on hand; 
Enter the number of people you're feeding; 
Enter the number of days you want your budget to last; 
Eliminate your dislikes and can't haves;
Choose your recipes;
Pick your store;
Receive your shopping list, and select your coupons.
Why should you use Stret¢h?:
Maximizes your food dollars;
Reduces food waste;
Displays meals that are within your budget from a database of over 500 recipes.
Generates your shopping list and recommended stores;  
Automatically recommends coupons that match what you actually have on your shopping list for additional savings.  
Simply stated, we want our users to experience the simplicity of being able to:Enter budget. Choose recipes they like. Get Shopping list & Coupons.  Live a better life. We won the Audience Choice Award at the Austin Tech Crunch Meet-Up.  We won tickets toDisrupt in San Francisco in September.  We also one of six finalists for the UnLtd USA incubation and mentorship program!  UnLtd will provide a year of support and $5k of Seed funding to the winner.  UnLtd USA will be a great place to truly test to see if our product and see the impact it is making in peoples lives before we scale up.  We'd like to get our MVP ready before attending Disrupt!  With your support, we can achieve this goal!  

For every $1,000 contributed, we will host a 1-on-1 Stret¢h cooking class for a family or individual in need.WHY DID YOU COME UP WITH THIS APP, LAUREN?Because Cheetos, Potato Chips, and Ground Beef changed my life.  A few years ago, when I was in graduate school, my youngest brother came to live with me.  I couldn't afford to feed him.  As a result, he had to sign up for food stamps.  In his first trip to the grocery store, he exhausted his entire month's budget.  After I finished yelling at him and cursing the system for being foolish enough to give him a full months funding in one shot... I realized it wasn't his fault.  Even though we didn't grow up in the same house, I personally knew it was hard to balance all of those decisions.  I grew up with my grandmother who was retired, diabetic, had heart disease, and cancer.  As a result, I often ate fast food for sustenance.  When I left home at 17, it was hard to budget and plan my meals, and yes, I had no concept of what was proper nutrition.  This life experience motivated me to begin Stretch Recipes to solve 5 key challenges:1)  I have only 'X' dollars and I need them to last 'Y' days before I get my next paycheck.2)  I want to eat something other than ramen, junk food, and/or the same 5 things my mother cooked for me.  3)  I always forget the coupons, or I'm an extreme couponer and if my mobile device would take care of it, I'd be in heaven.  4)  I'm trying to save for (insert) goal and the only place I can cut is my food and budget.  5)  I've recently had to change my diet.  My funds are limited and it's just a lot of stress trying to plan everything out.  HOW WILL YOUR CONTRIBUTION HELP?We're raising funds to help us to reach our next milestone, the MVP (Minimum Viable Product).  This MVP will enable us to test our product with a group of 100 people to fine tune for a great experience and make sure it's amazing when we go to launch the Beta.  These funds will cover:

Front-end design (UX and UI):  Easy to use and intuitive.  No clutter, no questions on how to use, and no numerous questions asked to get it to work.  We want only the best experience for our users.  

Hosting Costs:  We have a database and algorithms designed to help you maximize the experience.  We need hosting to ensure delivery and no down times.

Content Creation:  Pictures of food make it more fun to browse recipes.  We also need groceries and photographers.  Licensing fees quickly add up. 

Marketing and Research:  Truthfully, by contributing to this campaign, you effectively tell us the most important answers - Is what I am doing really needed?
Now, are you ready to Stret¢h your dollar to eat better and save more? RISKS AND CHALLENGESMy co-founder and I work full-time on this project – living off our small savings to bring our idea to life.  We believe in this that much.  We have designed your contribution levels to ensure that we can achieve the goals we have outlined above on time.We've estimated dates for delivery based on our current timeline for getting the product completed and launched and have aligned these to the target contribution levels.With your support and our commitment we plan to have the MVP completed by September 2014.We promise to  always keep you updated on our progress.Our TeamLauren Foster is the Founder, CEO/President of Stretch Recipes, Inc. an Austin based start-up.  A proud Chicago native and first generation college student and MBA, she is an Entrepreneur with over 15 years sum total experience in Media, Telecommunications, and Real Estate. Her hobbies include top golf, dancing, and traveling.It was recognizing the cyclical budget and nutrition patterns within her own life that led her to found Stretch Recipes, Inc.   She created Stret¢h because she wanted to make a tool that actually helps people with tight budgets maximize their dollar and have access to more nutritional recipes. She herself grew up in a low income household without the tools to learn how to budget for groceries, nor to prepare healthy meals.In August/September of 2013, the answer to providing help came in the thought to build an actual tool.  Already working in mobile apps, it seemed the best form to create a self-governed solution.  In November 2013, she began looking more into the problem and seeking help to pull it off.  In March 2013, she began landing partnerships with the SNAP program and local food banks in an effort to ensure the application would work for the tightest of budgets.  In early April, Lauren resigned from her full-time job in Real Estate Sales at Meritage Homes to found and build Stretch Recipes full-time.  Later that month, she also met CTO Ben Shank who would eventually become her Technical Co-Founder equally obsessed with creating a solution to help everyone eat better and save more.Ben Shank began programming when his third grade teacher cut a deal with him: pay attention in class and receive computer mentoring after school. He was later mentored by his little league baseball coach, the 23rd employee of Sun Microsystems, and further taught by a lead engineer of Microsoft's TerraServer (now MSR Maps) who also introduced him to Miles Davis.Ben went on to win a $250,000 sole-source software development contract with the State of Washington, integrate the computer vision subsystem leading to the first successful flight test and continuation of funding for ARGUS-IS, and lead development of AOL's internal content aggregation platform, spanning over 500 media properties including TechCrunch and Huffington Post.He is working to complete his MS in applied mathematics through Columbia University in 2015, and completed his GSD in the mid 1980's. Ben is an avid motorcyclist, a fun uncle, enjoys playing jazz and progressive rock guitar, and has read one Philip Roth novel.Acting on a deep-seated need to effect positive change in people's lives, Ben aligned immediately with Lauren's mission to maximize the choice of nutritional eating options to those with limited financial resources and left AOL to help realize her vision.FAQ'SWe've done our best to anticipate questions you may have.  Please feel free to message us through Indiegogo and we will be more than happy to reply and update the FAQ's.  Will this work for me if I am on Food Stamps?  Absolutely!  We are always working with partners to serve you.  When we say help everyone eat better and save more, we mean EVERYONE.  We have partners in Austin such as the Sustainable Food Center (SFC) and are always looking forward to growing more partnerships in markets that have similar programs.  What we love about SFC is that they offer Double-Dollar incentives at Farmers Markets for Seasonal Fresh Produce for SNAP and WIC recipients.  This means, your SNAP or WIC dollars go twice as far.  How are servings calculated?   We base servings on recommendations based on the recipe.  However, that's what this MVP is for, to test to ensure that the servings are not only appropriate, but don't leave you feeling shorted at meal times.Will you have Gluten-free Recipes?  YesWill you have Paleo Recipes? YesWill you have Vegan Recipes?  YesWill you have Normal every day recipes? YesIs this a diet fad app? NoWill you have recipes for certain medical conditions?  Yes.  We have identified 5 key medical restrictions we will roll out with the beta version.  These are common Food Allergies, Heart Disease, Diabetes, Liver Disease, and Celiac.  If there's a particular medical condition that we have overlooked, please feel free to email us and tell us about it at info@stretchrecipes.comWill you have cultural specific cuisine (ie. Indian, Mexican, Mediterranean, etc.)? Eventually, we will start with mostly American and move to add cultural cuisines as we go.  If you have specific Chef or recipe recommendations, don't hesitate to email us at info@stretchrecipes.com.  We are always on the hunt for dishes that are diverse, delicious, and serve you.I am not a good cook. We do our best to place recipes that are easy to make and also not hours to make (unless you can leave home while it prepares).  Additionally, we will launch a web class series for 101 that will help you get acclimated to the kitchen (knife safety, temperature recommendations, etc.) and also preparing most of the dishes within the App.  These classes will begin to appear on our website and within iTunes or YouTube in October 2014.  I hear you, but I am really not a good cook. Let's start with the crockpot and safety video demonstrations.  We'll have you cooking with smiles of joy around the dinner table in no time.  I'm single, will this App work for me?  Yes.I have a large family of more than 5, will this App work for me?  Yes.Can I use this at the grocery store?  Yes.Will this work if I'm just wanting to plan for one day?  Yes.  It's generally recommended to plan for at least 3 days to maximize and reduce food waste, but if there is no other choice, it will search for the options to best maximize what you have for the one day.Will this work if I'm just wanting to plan for a month?  Yes.  However, be sure to check your recipes.  If you are choosing a lot of fresh or organic produce, it is recommended to plan for at most 7 days at a time to reduce fresh produce food waste.  Why are you not an all or nothing campaign? We work off limited savings to bring this to life.  Every cent aides us in getting further along with our project.  I love what you're doing!  How can I help more in addition to my contribution?  SPREAD THE WORD!  TELL FRIENDS... AND EVERYONE CHECKING OUT AT THE CHECKOUT ABOUT THIS CAMPAIGN ;-)  ASK THEM, YOUR LOCAL GROCERS, EMPLOYERS AND PHYSICIANS TO GO A STEP FURTHER AND SUPPORT OUR CAMPAIGN.
